Website: Check out @user5. It seems easy to use, looks good, and is open source. I will switch one of my websites before the next renewal.
Signal: Check out cal.com. It's an open-source calendar service with integrations that allow you to schedule video calls using Element Call, Jitsi, etc. Signal is also supported, but I haven't tried yet whether it's for messages or video.
I can recommend @user6. E2EE, decentralized, open source.
